JOHANNESBURG – Heavy rain in parts of Pretoria and Johannesburg caused flooding on Monday afternoon. There was heavy traffic on Silver Lakes Road in Silver Lakes due to flooding. Some roads in and around Johannesburg have also been flooded. JHB - EXTREME !! #FLOODING RT @firstroad_brian @TrafficSA flooding on the N3 South at the Gillooly's pic.twitter.com/zvfVBP0Lf5 Heavy downpours have been forecast for the province. Motorists have been warned to drive with extreme caution and to expect heavy delays in affected areas. eNCA